ot just a numeric score.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"If explanation is model-generated, real failure is generation quality/format under real model behavior; mocks can always return ideal text and hide failures.","test_description":"Invoke real triage on representative symptom inputs and assert output includes a non-trivial natural-language rationale tied to symptoms/urgency (not only numeric code/template placeholder). Include repeated runs for consistency checks.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.06,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.7,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"Appointment is scheduled in first available slot matching urgency (high: same-day, medium: within 48h).","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Requires scheduler logic + shared calendar DB interaction. Pure unit tests can miss query/order bugs and slot-selection integration defects.","test_description":"Seed test calendar DB with controlled availability. Run scheduling for high and medium urgency through real scheduling module wiring; assert selected slot is earliest valid one and satisfies time-window rules.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":8,"description":"Scheduling does not double-book a time slot when two patients are processed concurrently.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Race conditions appear only with real concurrent access and DB constraints/transactions. Mocked single-thread tests can miss this.","test_description":"Run two concurrent scheduling requests targeting overlapping availability against the real test DB schema/constraints. Assert only one booking is created for the contested slot and the other request is re-routed/fails gracefully.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.66